I make it my business to share the good and the bad of parenting. I get complimented on my ability to keep my cool when dealing with the twin tantrums. It’s easier for me to keep my cool with the twins because they do not “know any better” right now, they are still learning.

My 3 yr old on the other hand is fully capable of understanding the simple requests that I ask of her. I find myself quickly loosing my patience when she chooses to do the opposite of what I am asking her, especially in situations where I need her to follow through with the request. 😤

Everyday I make an effort to keep my calm with her and when I mess up we talk it out and I address her feelings. This parenting thing is not easy and there are No PERFECT PARENTS, we are all humans who make mistakes.

Let me know if you can relate to this

Its timeeeeeee! Aminah is starting solids! 😃 I didnt even plan to start till 7 months but the way she was eyeballing and reaching for my yams last night let me know she was ready 🤣 

If you have been following me for a while you should be very familiar with my kids and their baby led weaning journeys. Each one of them took off running with it and I think Aminah will do the same 😄. 

If anyone is interested in starting baby led weaning with your little ones please be sure to look for these signs of readiness first:

🍓Sit up with little or no support.
🍓Hold his head steady.
🍓Reach out and grab things effectively.
🍓Take objects to their mouth quickly and accurately.
🍓Make gnawing and chewing movements

Be sure to go check out @babyledweanteam for more info!

Happy Baby Led Weaning! 😃

This Youtube video is a step by step guide to the Cry It Out method other wise known as The Ferber Method. (Link in bio)

This video was made for YOU if you are...

😴 a TIRED parent in desperate need of quality sleep 
🛌 a parent who just wants their bed to themselves again 👶 a parent who wants their baby learns the crucial skill to
self soothe
🤰an expecting mom trying to get a head start 
👨‍👩‍👦 a parent

So make sure you watch it from BEGINNING TO END!

We had our doubts about the Cry It Out method but I am so glad that we gave it a chance. All of our kids sleep in their own beds and have learned to safely self soothe. 

We would be lying if we said it was an easy journey, but we can say with 100% confidence that ITS WORTH A SHOT!
It’s recommended to start sleep training around 4 months but we know it’s never too late to start. We started crib/sleep training with our oldest when she was 11/2 years old and the twins started when they were 5 months. Both were two completely different experiences that ended in the same result so We know YOU CAN DO IT!

#sleeptraining #twinsleeptraining #twins #fourunderfour #theferbermethod #cryitout #cryitoutmethod #selfsoothing

This video is a glimpse into our daily reality. Don’t get me wrong some days are great and filled with so much communication, fun and hope. But most days are like this…

Jeff and I have four children under four and as you can imagine that can be very stressful to manage. We have found that having good communication and a well executed schedule is the only way we can survive the day. When communication and the schedule gets skipped then all hell breaks loose 🥴

Days like this ignite my mom guilt, because I want to do so much better than I did on this day. I wished I kept a cool head, I wish my tone was much nicer, and the list goes on and on. But this is life right?, God promised us that we will have ups and downs. Just keep your head up and do the best you can do ❤️

As I walked past my kids’ playroom, I saw their mess and felt an immediate urge to clean it up. But then, the sunlight pouring in through the window shone on their clutter in such a beautiful way that it made me pause.

It hit me! Every sticky surface, every misplaced toy, and even the pen marks on the walls were all precious memories that my kids had made. I sat down and chose to appreciate the beauty in their chaos.

These moments with my kids are quickly going away so fast 🥺 and I realized that I don’t want to miss out on creating memories just because of a little mess. At least not today… I’ll clean it tomorrow 😜

#toinfinityandbeyond #motherhood #motherhoodunplugged #momlife
